<td>	<p>
	The Ford Edge is a mid-size crossover SUV produced by Ford Motor Company. The production of this vehicle started in October 2006 and this was intended to be introduced in the market bearing the 2007 model year. However, the first unit of the Ford Edge reached the dealership's lot in December 2006 and this was due to the delay in its production triggered by the company's existing issues with some of its suppliers.<br />
<br />
But despite the delays in its production, the demand for the Ford Edge eventually increased. The increase in demand simply means that Ford has obtained a lot of revenues from this model. But as the years go by, some of the mid-size crossover SUV models started improve their features and this has prompted Ford Motor Company to conduct a major facelift on the Edge in 2010. <br />
<br />
After the facelift, the succeeding models were only subjected to regular upgrades and the 2012 Ford Edge has recently obtained a few changes such as the availability of the turbocharged "EcoBoost" 4-cylinder engine. The availability of an optional engine and other improvements implemented on the 2012 Ford Edge is expected to boost the vehicle's sales and take on the competition posed by other mid-size crossover SUV models.<br />
		</td>

	</tr>
<td>
